This is Go Tour, an introduction to the Go programming language.

Unless otherwise noted, the go-tour source files are distributed
under the BSD-style license found in the LICENSE file.

Contributions should follow the same procedure as for the Go project:
http://golang.org/doc/contribute.html

To test out this localised Go Tour on your machine, make sure that you have git
and hg (mercurial) installed on your system and do the following:

```
cd && mkdir go
export GOPATH=~/go
go get golang.org/x/net # ignore the errors
go get golang.org/x/tools
go get code.google.com/p/go-tour
cd $GOPATH/src/code.google.com/p/
rm -rf go-tour/
git clone https://github.com/kostich/go-tour-SR go-tour
cd go-tour/gotour/
go build; ./gotour
```
